cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.DM, cs.IT. 

The paper deals with geometric problems and their complexity, which suggests cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as the most likely category. The use of lower bounds and treewidth also suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as likely categories. The mention of fractal dimension and the use of probabilistic techniques suggest cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as a possible category. Finally, the use of the Exponential Time Hypothesis suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as another possible category.
